                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">FOUNDATION</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">The supportive brace for your mattress, a box spring is the most common.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">FRAME</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">A support system that provides a foundation for the box spring and mattress while also raising it off the ground.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">HANDMADE</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">Experienced craftspeople utilize traditional techniques to individualize luxury mattresses; this includes hand-woven quilting layers, hand-sewn edges and hand-tied box springs.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">HYBRID</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">Combines the comfort of memory foam or latex with the support of an innerspring. Both structures work together to conform to your body, relieve pressure and muscle tension and maintain correct alignment.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">INNERSPRING</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">The most common mattress, an innerspring combines supportive coils with cushioned upholstery.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">LATEX</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">Hypo-allergenic and breathable, latex mattresses are made of materials derived from the rubber tree. Boasting a long lifespan and good support, they lightly conform to the body&rsquo;s shape with a springy feel.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">MEMORY FOAM</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">Foam mattresses mold to your body, offering support while relieving pressure. They reduce motion transfer so you&rsquo;re less likely to be disturbed by movement on the other side of the bed.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">PILLOW TOP</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">A pillow top is constructed of extra layers of upholstery that are separately quilted and then sewn to the top of a mattress for added cushioning.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">TIGHT TOP</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">A tight top is a mattress that has a standard, non-pillow top.</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_separator"></div>
                                <div class="mattress_buying_guide_list_item">
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-title">TWO-SIDED<br>MATTRESS</span>
                                    <span class="mattress_buying_guide_desktop_list-description">Recommended for anyone sensitive to body impressions, these durable mattresses are upholstered on both sides and can be flipped regularly to extend the bed&rsquo;s life.</span>
